descp2: float, 1. by default If `algorithm='lasso_lars'` or `algorithm='lasso_cd'`, `alpha` is the penalty applied to the L1 norm. If `algorithm='threshold'`, `alpha` is the absolute value of the threshold below which coefficients will be squashed to zero. If `algorithm='omp'`, `alpha` is the tolerance parameter: the value of the reconstruction error targeted. In this case, it overrides `n_nonzero_coefs`.
